    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>DANONE BUYS NAYA</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Groupe Danone, leading seller of bottled water, buys assets of bankrupt Naya Inc (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A leading seller of bottled water, Groupe Danone of France, has doubled its North American capacity by buying the assets of Naya Inc. of Mirabel, Quebec, near Montreal. The purchase price was not disclosed. Established in 1986, Naya has been operating under bankruptcy protection for the last six months because it could not manage a $69 million debt. Groupe Danone plans to bring Naya's plant back to full production and add its brand name to those of Evian, Volvic and Crystal Springs.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard</p>
      </block>
